quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  42,32,"And among His signs are the ships sailing on the sea, like hills."
  42,33,"If He wills, He can calm the winds so the ships remain still on the sea surface; indeed in this are signs for every greatly enduring, grateful person."
  42,34,"Or He can ruin them due to peoples’ sins and He can forgive a great deal."
  42,35,"And for those who dispute regarding Our signs to realise; that they do not have a place to escape to."
  42,36,"Whatever you have received is only for usage in the life of this world, and that which is with Allah is much better and more lasting – for those who believe and rely upon their Lord."
  42,37,"And (for) those who avoid cardinal sins and indecencies, and forgive (even) when they are angry."
  42,38,"And those who obeyed the command of their Lord and kept the prayer established; and whose affairs are with mutual consultation; and who spend in Our cause from what We have bestowed upon them."
  42,39,"And those who take revenge when rebellion harms them."
  42,40,"The retribution of a harmful deed is the harm equal to it; so whoever forgives and makes amends, so his reward is upon Allah; indeed He does not befriend the unjust."
  42,41,"And there is no way of reproach against those who take revenge after being wronged."
  42,42,"Reproach is only against those who oppress people, and wrongfully spread rebellion in the land; for them is a painful punishment."
  42,43,"And indeed whoever patiently endured and forgave – then indeed these are acts of great courage."
  42,44,"And whomever Allah sends astray, there is no friend for him against Allah; and you will see the unjust when they behold the punishment saying, “Is there a way to return?”"
